Hey Terry... 

Tire shredding has been around for MANY years...we used it in the 60s
and 70s to get our ice racing tires to "bite"....dirt trackers still do
it today...truckers do it too, but with larger grooves...they call it
re-grooving... 
Not an artform you'll likely see in a "new" tire store, but it sounds
like you may have lucked out... 
Enjoy the ride... 

Den.
